snippet.title: React Native Portland Meetup - February 21, 2019 - Ryan Linton on Reactotron
snippet.description:
Ryan Linton of Infinite Red gave a demo of Reactotron, a free desktop app that allows inspection and debugging of React and React Native apps, at the React Native Portland meetup on Thursday, February 21, 2019.

You may also enjoy Darin Wilson's talk at Chain React 2018 (https://infinite.red/ChainReactConf) on Reactotron: https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=UiPo9A9k7xc

To learn more about Reactotron, check it out here:

https://infinite.red/reactotron

To learn more about Infinite Red, visit our website:

https://infinite.red

To learn more about the React Native Portland meetup or to join us next time, go here: 

https://www.meetup.com/React-Native-Portland

snippet.title: React Native Portland Meetup - March 21, 2019 - Frederick Engelhardt
snippet.description:
Talk title: React Native Expo - Production API Troubleshooting

Meetup link: https://www.meetup.com/React-Native-Portland/events/grggsqyzfbcc/

Frederick Engelhardt will be presenting an overview on Expo and an in-depth dive on some important Expo APIs and how to troubleshoot problems with having part of an app working on development but failing on production.

https://twitter.com/FEDevelops

Thank you Cvent for hosting the meetup at their office and providing food and drinks.

Expo: http://expo.io
